bootbootboot - boot Linux on qemu repeatedly until something fails
----------------------------------------------------------------------

It's good for diagnosing early boot problems in Linux and/or qemu,
especially problems which happen only rarely.

Read the instructions at the top of bootbootboot.c

Written by Richard W.M. Jones <rjones@redhat.com>
Licensed under the GNU General Public License v2 or above.

See also this which is similar but a bit different because it looks
for repeatable failures only:
https://people.redhat.com/~rjones/qemu-sanity-check/
